Package: eDNAstructure
Type: Package
Title: Dirichlet-Multinomial Mixture Models for eDNA Metabarcoding
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Pedro", "BDFP", email = "pedro_bdfp@hotmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Fits Bayesian Dirichlet-Multinomial Mixture (DMM) models to
    environmental DNA (eDNA) read count data from metabarcoding surveys. Given
    a sample-by-taxon count matrix and optional environmental covariates, the
    model identifies latent ecological communities, estimates their taxonomic
    compositions, and quantifies how environmental gradients drive community
    membership through a softmax regression, within a fully Bayesian framework
    using Stan. Includes a mechanistic simulation pipeline for generating eDNA
    survey datasets with known ground truth, and a suite of 'ggplot2'-based
    visualizations (STRUCTURE-style assignment bars, NMDS ordination, and
    prior-versus-posterior covariate effect plots).
